gomodel:SYNGO_4821  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2: immunofluorescence confocal imaging showed Cofilin in apposition to puncta of presynaptic marker VGLUT1, suggesting postsynaptic localization for Cofilin.\n\nFigure 3: Electron micrograph showing immunoperoxidase staining for cofilin in CA1.\n\nFigure 4: Immunogold labeling for cofilin in stratum radiatum of CA1.\n\nAuthors conclude that \"cofilin is localized to the PSD and the spine shell, and avoids the spine core\".. Experimental description: M&M: \"Experiments were carried out on 3-5 months old male Sprague-Dawley rats from Charles River (Raleigh, NC, USA).\"\n\nantibody:\n\"Primary antibodies used were polyclonal rabbit anti-cofilin (generated against the peptide KVFNDMKVRK, corresponding to an N-terminal region of human cofilin, Cytoskeleton, Denver, CO, USA, ACFL02, 0.5 μg/ml)\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2022-09-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4821" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

